pported Students (if applicable)</a></td><td><span tabindex="0">$994</span></td></tr><tr><td><a target="_blank" class="unswlinkvariant_fee" href="https://student.unsw.edu.au/fees-domestic-full-fee-paying">Domestic Students</a></td><td><span tabindex="0">$5970</span></td></tr><tr><td><a target="_blank" class="unswlinkvariant_fee" href="https://student.unsw.edu.au/fees-international">International Students</a></td><td><span tabindex="0">$5970</span></td></tr></tbody></table>","erg":[],"campus":{"name":""}},"additional_information":"","study_level_tooltip":"Undergraduate: A level of study that leads to the award of a Diploma, Advanced Diploma, Associate Degree or a Bachelor Degree (pass or honours).","campus":"Sydney","study_level_single":{"label":"Undergraduate","value":"ugrd"},"code":"CHEM1831","attributes":[{"name":"Introductory Course","code":"introductory_course","description":"This course is usually taken in the early part of a program and may be required as a pre-requisite before taking a more advanced course."}],"credit_points_header":"6 Units of Credit","eqivalents":[],"exclusion":[],"search_title":"CHEM1831 - Chemistry for Exercise Physiology","description":"<p>Designed for students in the Exercise Physiology program, this course covers the chemistry required to understand atomic and molecular structure, states of matter, thermodynamics, equilibrium chemistry in aqueous solution and introductory kinetics, the chemistry of organic compounds, stereochemistry, functional groups and their reactions especially amines, amides, acids and esters, redox chemistry of oxygen. Case studies and experiments relevant to health and exercise science are also included. The Chemistry in the course will prepare students for the Level II Biochemistry and Anatomy components of their programs. Assumed knowledge: A basic knowledge of Chemistry equivalent to the NSW Year 11 Chemistry syllabus. It is also recommended that BABS1201 be taken concurrently. Note: Students who have completed this course and wish to take further Chemistry courses should consult the School of Chemistry or their Program Advisor. This course is designed to cover a highly specific area of Chemistry and will not be useful for any students who wish to further their Chemistry knowledge.</p>","hb_assessments":[{"delivery_variation":{"cl_id":"9ed38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a96195f","name":"Blended in-person / online - Standard (usually weekly or fortnightly)"},"assessments":[{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Final Examination","assessment_type":{"label":"Examination","value":"examination"},"assessment_id":"4","weighting":"50","description":"<p>This is a traditional 2-hour exam, comprising a mixture of multi-choice and short-answer questions. Students do not automatically get feedback on their exam performance; they simply see their overall mark for the course. But students do have the option to make an appointment with the course coordinator to discuss their paper.</p>","learning_outcomes":[{"value":"CLO7","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961961","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO8","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961962","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO2","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961963","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO3","cl_id":"5ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961960","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO4","cl_id":"5ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961961","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO5","cl_id":"5ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961962","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO1","cl_id":"62d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961964","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO6","cl_id":"6ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961963","key":"code"}],"delivery_variations":[],"applies_to_all_delivery_variations":"true","cl_id":"22d3cfefdb4a9410358b403c3a96195a","links":[]},{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Laboratory","assessment_type":{"label":"Lab work","value":"lab_work"},"assessment_id":"3","weighting":"20","description":"<p>The School of Chemistry has recently changed the way its first year laboratory classes are assessed. Students are now assessed in real time, by their demonstrators, who observe and &#34;check off&#34; students&#39; physical skills in the lab. Half of the skills are &#34;core&#34;, meaning all students must gain them in order to pass the course. Altogether the &#34;core&#34; skills are worth 10% of the total marks for the course. Half of the skills are &#34;non-core (graded)&#34;, meaning that as students gain these skills, their lab mark increases gradually from 10% to 20% of the total marks for the course.</p>","learning_outcomes":[{"value":"CLO7","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961961","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO8","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961962","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO2","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961963","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO3","cl_id":"5ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961960","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO6","cl_id":"6ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961963","key":"code"}],"delivery_variations":[],"applies_to_all_delivery_variations":"true","cl_id":"aad3cfefdb4a9410358b403c3a961952","links":[]},{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Mid-semester Test","assessment_type":{"label":"Test","value":"test"},"assessment_id":"1","weighting":"10","description":"<p>This is a multi-choice test, comprising 20 questions, and administered under exam conditions (typically in the regular lecture venue). Students receive their mark via Moodle, and have the option to make an appointment with the course coordinator to discuss their paper.</p>","learning_outcomes":[{"value":"CLO2","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961963","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO3","cl_id":"5ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961960","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO4","cl_id":"5ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961961","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO1","cl_id":"62d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961964","key":"code"}],"delivery_variations":[],"applies_to_all_delivery_variations":"true","cl_id":"bed3cfefdb4a9410358b403c3a96197c","links":[]},{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Weekly Preparatory and Revision Quizzes","assessment_type":{"label":"Assignment","value":"assignment"},"assessment_id":"2","weighting":"20","description":"<p>Once a week, before the week&#39;s lectures, students log on to Moodle and complete an interactive, adaptive, self-paced online tutorial. These tutorials are designed to ensure that all students are &#34;up to scratch&#34; with the assumed knowledge for the course. Each tutorial concludes with a set of assessable questions, to which students get their results automatically. At the end of the week, students log onto Moodle again to complete a Revision Quiz. This operates on a similar format to the assessable part of the pre-week activity. At the end of semester, the pre- and post-week quizzes are worth a total of 20% of the marks of the course.</p>","learning_outcomes":[{"value":"CLO7","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961961","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO8","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961962","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO2","cl_id":"52d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961963","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO3","cl_id":"5ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961960","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO4","cl_id":"5ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961961","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO5","cl_id":"5ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961962","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO1","cl_id":"62d38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961964","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO6","cl_id":"6ad38fefdb4a9410358b403c3a961963","key":"code"}],"delivery_variations":[],"applies_to_all_delivery_variations":"true","cl_id":"c7d3cfefdb4a9410358b403c3a961982","links":[]}]}],"inactive_course_alert":null,"timetableURL":"http://timetable.unsw.edu.au/2021/CHEM1831.html","subject_sample_text_staticcontent":"To access course outline, please visit:","links":[]}
